 cytokine profiles in females with irritable bowel syndrome and extra-intestinal co-morbidity</article-title>. <source>Am J Gastroenterol</source><volume>105</volume>, <fpage>2235</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>2243</lpage>.<pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">20407431</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref16"><label>16</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Spiller</surname><given-names>R</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Aziz</surname><given-names>Q</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Creed</surname><given-names>F</given-names></name>, <etal>et al.</etal> (<year>2007</year>) <article-title>Guidelines on the irritable bowel syndrome: mechanisms and practical management</article-title>. <source>Gut</source><volume>56</volume>, <fpage>1770</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>1798</lpage>.<pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">17488783</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref17"><label>17</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Lakhan</surname><given-names>SE</given-names></name> &#x00026; <name><surname>Kirchgessner</surname><given-names>A</given-names></name> (<year>2010</year>) <article-title>Gut inflammation in chronic fatigue syndrome</article-title>. <source>Nutr Metab (London)</source><volume>7</volume>, <fpage>79</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>88</lpage>.</mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref18"><label>18</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>O'Mahony</surname><given-names>L</given-names></name>, <name><surname>McCarthy</surname><given-names>J</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Kelly</surname><given-names>P</given-names></name>, <etal>et al.</etal> (<year>2005</year>) <article-title>
<italic>Lactobacillus</italic> and <italic>Bifidobacterium</italic> in irritable bowel syndrome: symptom responses and relationship to cytokine profiles</article-title>. <source>Gastroenterology</source><volume>128</volume>, <fpage>541</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>551</lpage>.<pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">15765388</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref19"><label>19</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Schmulson</surname><given-names>M</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Pulido-London</surname><given-names>D</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Rodriguez</surname><given-names>O</given-names></name>, <etal>et al.</etal> (<year>2012</year>) <article-title>Lower serum IL-10 is an independent predictor of IBS among volunteers in Mexico</article-title>. <source>Am J Gastroenterol</source><volume>107</volume>, <fpage>747</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>753</lpage>.<pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">22270083</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref20"><label>20</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Chiba</surname><given-names>T</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Sato</surname><given-names>K</given-names></name>, <name><surname>Toya</surname><given-names>Y</given-names></name>, <etal>et al.</etal> (<year>2011</year>) <article-title>Serial changes in cytokine expression in irritable bowel syndrome patients following treatment with calcium polycarophil</article-title>. <source>Hepatogastroenterology</source><volume>58</volume>, <fpage>1527</fpage>&#x02013;<lpage>1530</lpage>.<pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">21940313</pub-id></mixed-citation></ref><ref id="ref21"><label>21</label><mixed-citation publication-type="journal"><name><surname>Ivanov</surname><given-names>S</given-names></name> &#x00026; <name><surname>Lind&#x000e9;n</surname><given-names>A</given-names></name> (<year>2009</year>) <article-title>Interleukin-17 as a drug target in human disease</article-title>. <source>Trends Pharmacol Sci</source><volume>30</volume>, <fpage>95</fpage>